summary: Well good evening, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and welcome to the Reputation Stadium Tour! You know, I’m not sure if you know...
text: Well good evening, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and welcome to the Reputation Stadium Tour! You know, I’m not sure if you know this, this is a very, very little known fact: I’m actually from Reading, Pennsylvania. And this, ladies and gentlemen, this is what I call a hometown show. You may also know this if you have recently looked at a calendar: today is Friday the thirteenth. See a lot of people are like, ‘Oh, Friday the thirteenth, that’s creepy, I don’t wanna stay on the thirteenth floor. Weird stuff happens on the thirteenth.’ But I’m a little bit different in that I think thirteen is the sickest number, the luckiest number, the coolest number. So, wouldn’t you think that if I were planning a tour, and I was thinking 'I’m so excited about going back and playing my hometown. What date should we play it?’ Just saying. You guys, you know, every single time I come back to Pennsylvania, as I get older, it gets more special to me. It’s always been so special to me being from Pennsylvania. But as I get older, every single time I come back, I get more and more emotional about it, and more proud to be from here. And you know, this is a state where I have people come up to me and say 'I saw you play at a fair when you were ten quite regularly.’ And the fact that it would go from that to getting to play two nights at this sold out stadium–I am so grateful. Thank you so much. So I know us on stage, we’re ready to put on a show, and I’m looking out at you; you seem very, very ready for a show tonight. Before we embark on this show, I just wanted to say you look absolutely beautiful. Like, even more beautiful than ever. It’s like you took it up a notch. You know what I mean?
source: Taylor’s opening speech in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania (July 13th, 2018)
